text: Anartia lytrea, or Godart's peacock, is a species of nymphalid butterfly found on Hispaniola and the Swan Islands of Honduras. It is a rare stray on Cuba. The butterfly has been known to occasionally stray into the lower keys of Florida. == References == == External links == * Protein sequencing * Anartia lytrea at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms Category:Anartia Category:Insects of Cuba Category:Insects of the Dominican Republic Category:Fauna of the Swan Islands Category:Taxa named by Jean- Baptiste Godart Category:Butterflies described in 1819 Category:Nymphalidae of South America
